Groping? oO
This just made my day, love ya man! 
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}

The same as it's always been. Group up and kill him when he tries to make a play. Rengar can't jump into 5 people (unless he is stupidly fed, and even then, hard CC wrecks him). He will obliterate your whole team if he gets the chance to do it, so don't give it to him. As long as you don't give him the 1v1 that he is trying to get, you can CC him down and kill him before he can do anything, as his stealth no longer allows him to get too close without revealing himself.
TL;DR - "Group up and hit it till it dies!"
{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}}

My friend, you are working off the assumption that he is already fed and snowballing out of control. At that point you can replace "Rengar" with any snowballing champion and the results will be the same. Don't give him the chance to snowball. If he's coming for you you get the animation way ahead of time. Control wards will find him when he stealths.
The full AD assassin Rengar does an assload of damage, but explodes pretty much instantly if he gets CC-ed and focused. That being said, at the time I wrote my post above, I didn't know that Tank Rengar is even more broken than full AD. Good job to whoever designed that option. 
{{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}}

{{item:3157}} 

Seriously, if you can use the AP, build it. Also stay away from bushes (No fighting in the jungle!) Lastly, stick closely to your entire team. CC isn't counterplay, it's just regular play as it affects all champions. He can also get rid of it :l Even so, use CC on him. A team should always have CC. 

I know this isn't actually a legitimate question and it's mostly a "nerf Rengar" thread, and that this comment will be buried in downvotes. I'm not saying Rengar is healthy, but rather just answering your question to the best of my ability.
